# shadcn/ui + Tailwind Project Rules

This project is **Next.js 14 App Router**, not Vite.

## Use the existing stack

- Package manager: `npm`.
- Tailwind is already configured through `tailwind.config.ts`, `postcss.config.mjs`, and `app/globals.css`.
- shadcn/ui is already configured through `components.json` and `components/ui/*`.
- Prefer existing `components/ui/*` primitives before adding new UI dependencies.
- Use `framer-motion` only for meaningful interaction, reveal, or premium polish.

## Do not do this

- Do not install Vite or `@tailwindcss/vite`.
- Do not replace the Next.js Tailwind setup with Vite setup instructions.
- Do not add Magic UI or Aceternity-style packages unless the existing Tailwind/shadcn stack cannot accomplish the section.
- Do not introduce new styling systems for one-off sections.

## Homepage UI workflow

- Build premium sections with Tailwind utilities, shadcn-style primitives, and existing motion patterns.
- Keep mobile responsive layouts first.
- After homepage UI edits, run `npm run build` and verify `/` returns HTTP 200.
